CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 8, 1941, pg. 12, reads: "Pocohontas [Pocahontas] in a Pensive Mood - Miss Pocohontas [Pocahontas] G. Crews, 600 S, Duquesne Avenue, city, who is studying accounting and hopes to be a career girl some day. Along with her many school activities, she finds time to play a good game of golf when the weather permits.  There has been no indication of any "John Smith" in Pocohontas' life so far.  But she does have many admirers. (Harris Photo)."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Pocahontas G. Crews wearing dark velvet dress with triangular brooch, posed in front of light colored background, in Harris Studio
